# Compress memory files (.md, .txt)

Goal: shorter token footprint; **preserve** technical truth, code, URLs, structure.

## Allowed targets

Natural language: `.md`, `.txt`, extensionless prose. **Never** compress: `.py`, `.js`, `.ts`, `.json`, `.yaml`, `.yml`, `.toml`, `.env`, `.lock`, `.css`, `.html`, `.xml`, `.sql`, `.sh`.

Skip `*.original.md` backups.

## If repo has compressor CLI

Skill lived beside `scripts/`. If present: `cd <that-dir> && python3 -m scripts <absolute_filepath>` — CLI validates/retries; on failure leave original.

If **no** CLI in workspace: compress in-editor using rules below; save backup as `<name>.original.md` before overwrite.

## Strip from prose

Articles; filler (just/really/basically…); pleasantries; hedging; fluff connectors. Prefer imperatives. Merge duplicate bullets.

## Preserve exactly

Markdown fenced code blocks — verbatim order, spacing, comments. Inline backtick spans. URLs, paths, commands, env vars, versions, proper nouns, heading text, list nesting, tables (compress cell text only if meaning intact), YAML frontmatter structure.

## Critical

Do not alter anything inside fences or backticks. Compress only outside code regions.
